{
  "texts": [
    "We believe that the potential of the powerful representation capability of complex structures has not been fully explored yet in time series anomaly detection tasks.",
    "We strongly advocate prioritizing the refinement of module design or loss function in order to enhance the models' resilience to noise and their capacity for generalization.",
    "Thus complicated backbones can better leverage their expressive power for temporal features without overfitting to noise.",
    "Performance in Fine-Grained ScenariosMerely referring to aggregated data at the granularity of datasets is insufficient to gain a profound understanding of the model's performance.",
    "We carry out a fine-grained comparison of model performance from the perspectives of both learning schema and anomaly type."
  ]
}